        <div class="col-md-6  order-1 order-md-2" style="font-family:'Pacifico', cursive;color:#e5eff7;">
            <h1 class="mt-3 text-center">What you’ll need:</h1>
            <p class="mt-3 px-5" >
                <ul class="px-5  py-3">
                    <li>One Aeropress.</li>
                    <li>One Aeropress Filter.</li>
                    <li>17g coffee (approximately 8.5 teaspoons) in AeroPress grind.</li>
                    <li>One Cup.</li>
                    <li>One Tablespoon.</li>
                    <li>One Kettle.</li>
                    <li>230ml water (1.5 tablespoon less than 1 cup) at 90°C (5:30 minutes off boil).</li>
                    <li>Scales, if possible, otherwise follow eye measurements. </li>

                </ul>        
            </p>

        </div> 

       </div>

   </div>
   <div class="container-fluid">
       <div class="row">
        
        <div class="col-lg-6  " style="font-family:'Pacifico', cursive;color:#e5eff7;">
            <h1 class="mt-4 text-center">Brewing Recipe</h1>
            <p class="mt-3 px-5" >
                <ul class="px-5  py-3">
                    <li> Using your Aeropress the inverted way, pre-wet filter paper in the filter basket.</li>
                    <li>Add 17g coffee.</li>
                    <li>Start timer and add 80ml of 90℃ water.</li>
                    <li>Stir a few times to wet all the grinds and leave for 20 seconds.</li>
                    <li>Add 70ml more of 90℃ water and stir vigorously 20 times. </li>
                    <li>Screw on the filter cap and leave until the timer is at 1 minute.</li>
                    <li>At 1 minute, flip Aeropress onto the cup, and slowly press over 1 minute.</li>
                    <li>Top up with 80ml hot water.</li>

                </ul>        
            </p>

        </div> 
